title.undefined: Circular Economy Ontology Network (CEON) - Actor Module

description.undefined: The Actor module of CEON (Circular Economy Ontology Network).

coversRequirements.value: In addition to requirements covered by imported ODPs, covers the following requirements from Onto-DESIDE D3.2: C0-1, C0-2, C3-4, T3-4
In addition to requirements covered by imported ODPs, covers the following requirements from Onto-DESIDE D3.1: C0-1, C0-2, C3-4, T3-4

title.value: Circular Economy Ontology Network (CEON) - Actor Module

comment.undefined: The role(s) of an actor in a Circular Value Network, which is a specific type of collaboration.
The relation where the role of the actor is the buyer of a certain resource.
The generic relation representing the particpation of a resource in some relation. For example, it can be specialized to represent a reified version of an object or data property.
The role(s) of an actor in relation to a resource.
Represents the participation of objects in some situation.

A participation-relation, that represents the participation of an actor in a CVN with a certain role. For instance, a specific company playing the role of recycler in a certain flow of a CVN. The participation may also be related to a certain time (or time interval).

Participation of a certain actor in a certain process, with a certain role. For instance, a certain department of a recycling company having the role of quality controllant, or material sorter, in a certain recycling process. The participation may also be given a time, e.g. a start and end time.
The relation where the role of the actor is the producer of a certain resource.

A relation between a resource, an actor, and the role the actor has in relation to the resource. For instance, the role of owner that a certain actor takes for a certain resource for a certain period of time. Or the seller of a certain resource, until that resource has been sold, and the actor no longer has that role in relation to the resource.

The relation involving the role of a certain actor with respect to a value network or a process in such a network, e.g. an organisation (actor) acting as the recycler (role) in a glass recycling value netowrk (network) at a specific point or period in time. Or an organisation (actor) acting as the dismantler (role) in a dismantling step of a building deconstruction process (process step) at a specific point or period in time.
The relation where the role of the actor is the viewer of a certain resource.

comment.en: Person or organization that can affect, be affected by, or perceive itself to be affected by a decision or activity. To “perceive itself to be affected” means the perception has been made known to the organization.

comment.undefined: The roles of an actor involved in a collaboration.
Something that the actor is capable of doing, e.g. perfomring a certain role in a process, based on some properties, such as access to infrastructure, resources and know-how.
The relation where the role of the actor is the seller of a certain resource.
The relation where the role of the actor is the supplier of a certain resource.
The relation where the role of the actor is the consumer of a certain resource.
A collaboration between a set of actors.
The type of an actor, e.g. the type of company, or a specific subtype based on the organisations capabilities.
An infrastructure refers to facilities, services, or systems for participations to function.

definition.value: A coherent set of direct positions in space. The positions are held within a Spatial Reference System (SRS).

comment.undefined: The relation where the role of the actor is the reseller of a certain resource.
The relation where the role of the actor is the user of a certain resource.

comment.en: Person or group of people that has its own functions with responsibilities, authorities, and relationships to achieve its objectives. The concept of organization includes, but is not limited to sole-trader, company, corporation, firm, enterprise, authority, partnership, charity or institution, or part or combination thereof, whether incorporated or not, public or private (e.g. foundation, union, association, agency, municipality, region, country, intergovernmental agencies). A group of organizations can also be considered as	an organization that has, alone or collectively,their own objectives.

comment.undefined: The relation where the role of the actor is the owner of a certain resource.
The relation where the role of the actor is the manufacturer of a certain resource.

A role that an actor can take in a specific context. Applies both to roles in the context of resources, such as owner, manufacturer, reseller etc. of that resource, as well as roles in relation to a circular value network, such as recycler, dismantler, transporter etc., in relation to a material flow.
Location of an organisation
The relation where the role of the actor is the issuer of a certain resource.
The relation where the role of the actor is the provider of a certain resource.
The relation where the role of the actor is the updater of a certain resource.
The role(s) of an actor involved in a process.
An agent able to act in the context of a circular value network, e.g. an organisation, person.
The type of the actor.
The point in time when something took place or was valid.
Relates some properties to the capability, such as the parameters of it, or the needed resources.
The end of a time interval.
Relates to the actor holding the capability.
Defines the location of an actor or resource.

comment.undefined: Represent code of a country's name.
Participating object in a resource participation. This is part of a resource participation that can be a directional relation, and the participating object is the end point of the relation.
Represent name of a city
Represent that an organisation has some locations.
The extent of this capability, e.g. stating whether there are limist to the capability, such as a maximum amount or size of something.
The resource that this participation relation relates to, i.e. for which the actor holds the specified role.
Represent postal code

definition.value: The GeoJSON serialization of a Geometry.

comment.undefined: The collaboration or process that this participation relates to.
Represent name of a country
Holds the value of the role of the participant in this participation relation.
Holds the value of the infrastructure involved in this participation relation.
Represent address of a street, including e.g., street number and name
The Global Location Number (GLN) is part of the GS1 systems of standards.
Participating subject in a resource participation. This is part of a resource participation that can be a directional relation, and the participating subject is the starting point of the relation.
Holds the value of the actor involved in this participation relation.
An actor participates in a collaboration based on that it has some capability that is useful for the collaboration.
In order for an actor to have a capability, it needs to have certain resources, e.g. materials, infrastrucutre, know-how, information etc.

definition.value: The WKT serialization of a Geometry.

comment.undefined: The start of a time interval.
